Instagramers Networth

Chastyn Smith

Introduction

Social media has now become an essential role in all of our lives. The various social media platforms such as Twitter, Instagram, Facebook, and etc are transforming how we keep up with politics, hear of job offers, keep up with celebrities, and promote our businesses. With traditional social and informational outlets like newspapers, magazines, and physical books on the decline it is now necessary for those living to be update with how to work technology and social media. This is a simple task for the younger generations but, does this impose a disadvantage for the older generation present? Most musicians choose to promote their music via social media since it is the fastest way for information to be released and spread, but is this necessary? For my project I chose to investigate the correlation, if any between musicians net worth and their Instagram usage. I hypothesize that the musicians who use Instagram the least have a higher net worth. Within the musicians who use Instagram I hypothesize that the genre of music that they specialize in plays a role in how much they use Instagram. I hypothesize that those in the heavy metal genre use Instagram less than those from pop but those from the heavy metal genre have a higher net worth than those from the pop genre. inference for the net worth and followers by genre.

Methods

To collect this data I took the current top 100 musicians and recorded their net worth and genre of music they made or make. I then recorded the amount of followers each musician had and the number of posts they had. The net worth value is in millions except for Paul McCartney and Andrew Weber whose net worths are in the billions and the followers unit is thousands. To see the average net worth of those with Instagram by genre a bar graph will be used.

Results

Instagram usage versus networth

Here I wanted to see the correlation between the amount of posts made and the networth of the musicians. This graph shows that the musicians with higher networths post more on instagram. We even see that there is a positive correlation between the two by the slope.

This graph shows the networth of the musicians in the genres pop and heavy metal when compared to country music. We see that the pop genre musicians networths are way more than the heavy metal genre musicians when the baselin is country music.

Conclusions

Here, you should summarize the results of the three hypothesis tests. Indicate whether there was (i) no significant effect, (ii) an effect in the direction you expected, or (iii) a significant but opposite effect than the one you expected. Write several sentences putting these results into context (what do the confidence intervals and point estimators mean in practice?).

These three tests did and did not support some of my hypothesis. Instagram posts did increase with networths although there were some outliers in the data. As far Instagram usage the data did support my claim. The graph did show that pop musicians use Instagram more than heavy metal musicians. Although the baseline for this test was country music, we see that the difference in posts for heavy metal musicians compared to pop musicians was less. the data does not allow this statement to be made certain since the confidince intervals include zero therefore showing that the difference may or not be there for pop and heavy metal versus country music. For the average networth by genre I predicted that the heavy metal genre would have a higher networth than the pop genre, this was not supported. Again although compared to country music, the decrease from the average networth of country music musicians to that of pop is significantly less than that of havy metal. Again, this statement cannot be made with certainty since the confidence intervals for both pop and heavy metal include zero, which may negate this difference.
